About Me

My name is Tripp Parham. I am from Raleigh, North Carolina. I hold a Bachelors of Science in the Biological Sciences and an Associates Degree in Network Security form ECPI University. I have recently certified in Full-Stack web development at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. I am currently seeking to launch a bright career as a Full Stack Web Developer.

Prior to learning to code, I worked as a hardware engineer for VCE, now Dell/EMC. My job was to set up EMC storage arrays in different configurations based on software development and testing needs based on service tickets opened by internal customers. My duties included rack and stack, equipment maintenace and rotation, and advanced troubleshooting.

I am interested in learning about new opportunities and can be reached through this portfolio, by email: tripp.parham@gmail.com,{" "} {" "} through GitHub, or through{" "} LinkedIn.
